Dear Martin,

Thank you for reaching out. To investigate why the Audit Data View in PingCastle Pro is not displaying example findings while the Free version does, we need to check the raw data in the XML files.

Could you please provide the following?

  *   The XML files from both the Free version and the Pro version for comparison
  *   The trace logs from the PingCastle Pro Web Portal to check if there are any errors in processing the XML (PingCastle.exe --healthcheck --log)
  *   Confirmation on whether any filters are applied in the Audit Data View that could be hiding findings
Once we review the data, we will provide guidance on how to resolve this. Let us know if you need any assistance retrieving the files.

Best regards,

TextBody:
Hi Nimesha,

Thank you for the update.

To further analyze the issue, I would need to confirm a few details:

Permissions Used to Generate the Report

	Was the free version report run with Domain Admin or limited user permissions?
	Running it with limited permissions may result in missing details in the findings.

Verify XML File Integrity


	Can you confirm if the XML file opens correctly in a text editor (Notepad++, VS Code)?
	If the file appears incomplete or corrupted, we may need to regenerate it.

Troubleshooting Steps


	Try re-importing the XML and check for any import errors in the PingCastle logs.
	If possible, generate a new free version report on HBD.INT with elevated permissions and compare it to the current XML.
	Ensure that the XML is not being modified or truncated during transfer.

If you can provide the XML file, I can check if it was generated correctly and help identify any issues. Let me know how you‚Äôd like to proceed.

Best regards,
Iulia Apatachioaei
Sr. Support Engineer

Hello Martin, I am glad that we were able to get your issue resolved. The following is a summary of the ticket for your records. Symptom The audit data view in the PingCastle Pro portal did not display example findings for each topic after uploading an XML file. Cause The initial scan was conducted without the --full parameter, which is required to perform an in-depth analysis and populate the audit data view with example findings. Resolution Re-running the PingCastle scan with the --full parameter ensured that all relevant findings were captured. After uploading the new XML file, the audit data view now correctly displays example findings for each topic. Following this email, you will receive an automated confirmation that the case is closed, along with the ability to re-open the case if any related errors return. In addition, you will also receive a separate email with a survey where you can let us know how we did. Feel free to leave any feedback via the survey link!
